## Diagnosis

The `micro` rendering mode is being triggered for tiles in the 32–64px width range, shrinking category labels to ~8px. This is a legibility anti-pattern: text that small is not readable by humans and conveys no information. The tile is essentially broken at that size.

---

## Root Cause

**AP-072 — "Graceful Degradation Through Illegibility"**: progressively scaling font size toward zero instead of switching to a non-text representation. The component is trying to show text at every size, which means it shows *unreadable* text at small sizes rather than omitting it entirely.

The `micro` mode exists as a false middle ground between "show label" and "show nothing" — it makes the tile *look* like it has content while delivering none.

---

## Fix

### `components/KnowledgeTreemap/KnowledgeTreemapTile.tsx`

Remove the `micro` branch entirely. Tiles narrower than 64px get no label — just the colour block. Tiles 64px and wider get the normal label at full size.

```tsx
// Before — three modes, one of which is illegible
type RenderMode = 'full' | 'compact' | 'micro';

function getRenderMode(width: number, height: number): RenderMode {
  if (width < 32) return 'micro';        // ← broken
  if (width < 64) return 'compact';
  return 'full';
}

// Inside JSX
{mode === 'micro' && (
  <span className="text-[8px] leading-none truncate">{category}</span>
)}
{mode === 'compact' && (
  <span className="text-xs leading-tight truncate">{category}</span>
)}
{mode === 'full' && (
  <span className="text-sm leading-snug">{category}</span>
)}
```

```tsx
// After — two modes: show label or show nothing
type RenderMode = 'visible' | 'hidden';

function getRenderMode(width: number, height: number): RenderMode {
  // Below this threshold the tile cannot host readable text.
  // Show nothing rather than show illegible text.
  if (width < 64 || height < 24) return 'hidden';
  return 'visible';
}

// Inside JSX
{mode === 'visible' && (
  <span className="text-sm leading-snug truncate">{category}</span>
)}
// mode === 'hidden' → render the colour block only, no text node at all
```

---

### `components/KnowledgeTreemap/KnowledgeTreemap.tsx`

If the parent passes a `minTileWidth` prop that allows tiles below 64px, clamp it:

```tsx
// Before
const MIN_TILE_WIDTH = 32;

// After
const MIN_TILE_WIDTH = 64; // tiles narrower than this carry no label (see KnowledgeTreemapTile)
```

---

### Remove the Tailwind class from the safelist

If `text-[8px]` was added to `tailwind.config.ts` or a safelist for this purpose, remove it:

```ts
// tailwind.config.ts
safelist: [
  // Remove this line:
  // 'text-[8px]',
],
```

---

### `components/KnowledgeTreemap/KnowledgeTreemap.stories.tsx`

Add a story that explicitly validates the small-tile case so a future contributor can see what correct behaviour looks like:

```tsx
export const SmallTiles: Story = {
  args: {
    /* force many categories so tiles get small */
    data: generateManyCategories(40),
  },
  play: async ({ canvasElement }) => {
    const tiles = canvasElement.querySelectorAll('[data-tile]');
    tiles.forEach((tile) => {
      const label = tile.querySelector('[data-tile-label]');
      const rect = tile.getBoundingClientRect();
      if (rect.width < 64) {
        // Tiles below threshold must have NO label rendered
        expect(label).toBeNull();
      } else {
        expect(label).not.toBeNull();
      }
    });
  },
};
```

---

## Principle

> **Never render text below the legibility threshold as a degradation strategy.**
> If a container cannot host readable text at the system's minimum font size (typically 12–14px for body copy), **remove the text entirely** rather than scaling it down. A blank coloured tile is honest — it communicates "this tile is too small to label". Sub-threshold text is dishonest — it looks like information but delivers none, and it fails WCAG SC 1.4.4 (Resize Text) and SC 1.4.12 (Text Spacing). The correct design primitive is a **binary switch** (label present / label absent), not a continuous font-size ramp.
